      "content": "that makes sense for the economic side. but for the debate, i really need to go deeper into the social logic they used. like, how would an advocate back then justify the idea that separating different racial groups into specific zones was actually \"good\" for social cohesion or preserving culture? i need to understand the specific rationale for why segregation was presented as a way to prevent social friction or protect community identity. can you give me some of the most common arguments used to defend that kind of separation?",
